data.text:
The Svenska HÃ¶garna lighthouse is a so-called Heidenstam lighthouse, named after its inventor Gustav von Heidenstam. The lighthouse is 18 m tall and was constructed in 1874. The present lighthouse replaced a simple beacon that sat in the same location. There's an inscription in the rock beneath the lighthouse in remembrance of the old beacon. The lighthouse is owned and operated by the Edward SjÃ¶blom foundation.
